Adding top of page code snippets

Removed link to Community Forum from Dropdown

The community dropdown is meant for users to navigate the community of the organization - community forum link to Tendenci's community forum is out of place in this dropdown.

Remove famfam home icon from admin menu

Per conversation with eschipul removing home icon from admin menu
The home icon causes confusion for user. .
Through this iteration of software and in past versions, the home icon gets linked to different places.  Additionally causes confusion when placed to left of Tendenci logo - clients assume home icon should take them to homepage of site but instead has been linked to dashbord or user profile in past.

Update One Column With Header.html

Adding in tags to allow option for pulling in content from apps including events, articles, news, resumes, jobs, directories, pages

Update Two Column Left Newsletter.html

Adding tags to all option of pulling in content from apps including events, articles, news, directories, jobs, resumes

Update Subway Line Newsletter.html

Adding tags to allow option to pull in content from apps including, news, articles, events, resumes, jobs, directories, pages

Update Seagulls Newsletter.html

Adding module tags in newsletter default to provide option to feed in modular content for pages, jobs, resumes, events, articles, directories, news

Update Holiday Night Lights Newsletter.html

Adding template tags to default newsletter to provide option to pull in app feeds.

Update Big City Newsletter.html

Adding tags for modules: articles, calendars, directories, jobs, resumes, pages to default template. This will allow users to have access to pull in content if they so choose.

Update _apps_dropdown.html

Reports item was not not linking anywhere, updated from # to /reports

Update _apps_dropdown.html

Moved Help Files Icon to top of Row 2. 

Changed helpfiles link to pull local help files module instead of linking to the Tendenci Help Files Page

Update _apps_dropdown.html

Added icon for "Events" to Content dropdown based on user feedback

Update custom.css

Change to style on .logo img
With width on .logo .img set to 100% the image was automatically resizing to take up 100% of the col area which distorted the image. 
By changing max-width to 100% image size is restricted without distortion and image stays responsive.
